LS(1)

NAME
    ls - list directory contents

SYNOPSIS
    ls [path]

DESCRIPTION
    ls lists entries in path, or the current directory when path is omitted.

    Directories are shown with a trailing slash. File sizes are printed for
    regular files when the filesystem provides them.

EXAMPLES
    ls
    ls /usr/share/man/man1

SEE ALSO
    tree(1), pwd(1), cd(1)
